post_text:
We will begin scheduling students for the upcoming school year beginning next week. Students will report by grade level at specified times and only at those times. Students that do not attend the specified times will not have a schedule prepared for the beginning of the school year.

Monday August 10th Seniors will report at 1 oclock, and Juniors will report at 3 oclock.

Tuesday August 11th 8th graders will report at 5:30 and 7th graders will report at 7 oclock.

Wednesday August 12th Sophomores will report at 1 oclock and Freshmen will report at 3 oclock.

Schedules have been emailed to each student and also posted on Facebook. And can also be picked up at the front entrance of the high school at any time. I recommend students have 3 schedules prepared prior to coming to set up their schedules. This will help the scheduling process.

Parents are welcome to attend and help with their child's schedule.

We look forward to seeing everyone next week.

post_text:
Vaccination Requirements for the 2020-2021 school year:
8th grade students will need a TDAP and MCV vaccination.
12th grade students will need a second MCV vaccination.
You will need to acquire these vaccines before the start of the school year, please do not wait until the last minute to get these, because the health department often runs out in mid-August. You can obtain these at our local health department, free of cost, on Tuesdays or Wednesdays, put you must call and make an appointment this year due to the social distancing requirements. You can also obtain shots at the SMCHC Thayer clinic the coat would be on a sliding scale. Please remember to bring your child‚Äôs immunization record when you go to get your vaccines. If you have any questions you can call the school at 264-4600 ext. 334 and I will do my best to help you. Hope you are having a great summer.
Traci Willison, school nurse.

Thayer Bands
May 22 at 3:00 PM ¬∑

Hey everybody,

While there is still some uncertainty about how next school year/marching season is going to look, we are going to plan to have everything as normal unless we are instructed otherwise. There will inevitably be some changes but the extent of those changes remains to be seen.

That being said, we will have:

-Leadership Camp- Monday July 20th

-8am-12pm

-Percussion and Color Guard camp July 20th-July 24th.

-7/20 2pm-6pm

-7/21-7/24 8am-2pm

-Full Band Camp-August 3rd-August 7th

-8am-4pm

Exact times may change

Also: Over the course of the summer, I would like to have small rehearsals periodically to start getting ready for camp and marching season.

During these rehearsals, we will spend as much time as possible outside and obey all social distancing and number restrictions.

I will post times here as well as through remind when those are set.

These rehearsals are not mandatory but will be a great time to see some fellow band members and start working towards next season.

March 25, 2020

Thayer Students meal distribution for the Week of March 30th

Meal distribution will be Sunday, March 29th from 2:00-4:00 P.M. at the Elementary. Students will be given 5 days worth of breakfast and 5 days worth of lunches at that time. This is a drive through pick-up.

If a family needs us to deliver their meals, please call (417) 264-4600 Friday, March 27th from 8:00 A.M. to 10:00 A.M and choose elementary or high school office extension and let them know your family name, how many students, and your address. These meals will be delivered on Sunday, during the 2:00 to 4:00 P.M. window.

Thank you!

Boys & Girls Club of the Greater West Plains Area- Thayer Branch
March 20 at 9:14 PM ¬∑

Boys & Girls Club of Thayer will be offering an evening meal and a snack to all kids in the community of Thayer up to the age of 18 years old.

We will be handing out meals Monday March 23 thru March 27th from 5pm to 7pm at the Thayer Elementary. We also will be doing delivery of meals within a 5 mile radius of the school.

If you need meals delivered please call 417-280-2582 or 417-274-2418.

Kids will get a breakfast and lunch thru the school and then they can also get a dinner and snack thru the Boys & Girls Club. That's 4 meals a day.

Our goal is to keep as many bellies full as we can during the next 2 weeks.

Thank you.

post_text: The Thayer R-II School District would like to share an update on the plan the district is working on in respect to the Coronavirus/COVID-19 pandemic. We are in close communication with our local health department, and we continue to monitor websites of the Centers for Disease Control and Prevention (CDC), the World Health Organization (WHO) and Missouri Department of Health and Senior Services (MODHSS) in order to keep current on this evolving situation. The following link will give you the updated information: http://thayer.k12.mo.us/departments/health_servies
